title: For Sale/Trade:  WW2 Nazi S.A.C.M. SACM 1935A Waffen Proofed WWII
postcontent: This is an original French S.A.C.M. model 1935A pistol. The pistol was made during WW2 after Nazi occupation of France - and has waffen WaA251 proof stamped on the frame and barrel. This pistol has an anodized black painted finish that is in about 80-85%condition. Only the SACM used this process of finishing guns rather than the more common bluing process many this a fairly unique Axis Pistol. There is some use and aging wear. The finish is thinning on the frame near the serial number, waffen stamp, and model legend. The frame also has some spotting patina and light beginning signs of rust on the front and back straps. The slide has some minor surface wear as well on the right side of the slide near the ejection port and top of the slide. The photos accurately depict the condition. The grips and magazine are original and period correct as are all parts on this piece. The bore is about an 8.5 out of 10 with some very light patina on the grooves but overall a clean bore. There are no import marks or major flaws - mechanically sound. Guaranteed original and authentic - C&R eligible.  This gun will also come with 60 rounds of original surplus ammo and 5 rounds of reloadable(with slight modification) brass
